Cell.Text: Gods. A woman attacked in broad daylight. | Are you all right? Did you see what happened?

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysForceGreetEntryTopic

Cell.Text: [S] G|I'm so sorry. I hope the Eight give you more peace in the future.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysForceGreetResponseTopic01: I was right there. He almost killed me.

Cell.Text: [S] G|The Forsworn? Strange. Well, I hope the Eight give you more peace in the future, for what it's worth.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysForceGreetResponseTopic02: I heard some shouting about the Forsworn. That was it.

Cell.Text: My note? No, that's yours. Must have fallen out of your pocket.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysNotAtShrineNoteTopic: Is this your note? What does this mean?

Cell.Text: I'm sorry to drag you into Markarth's problems, but after that attack in the market, I'm running out of time. | You're an outsider. You're dangerous-looking. You'll do.
Changed your mind? Ready to find out the truth about Markarth?

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysBlockingShrineBranch01EntryTopic

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> You want answers? Well so do I. So does everyone in this city. | A man goes crazy in the market. Everyone knows he's a Forsworn agent. Guards do nothing. Nothing but clean up the mess.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysBlockingShrineBranch01Topic01: "I'll do"? What are you talking about?

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> Oh, I think you dropped this. Some kind of note. Looks important.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysForceGreetResponseWalkAwayTopic: (Walk Away)

Cell.Text: You don't have to say sorry to me. I just hope the Eight bring us more peace in the future.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysForceGreetResponseTopic03: I must have missed it. Sorry.

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> Oh, I think you dropped this. Some kind of note. Looks important.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysForcegreetInvisible: (Invisible Continue)

Cell.Text: Huh. Not sure. I don't worship Talos, myself. | I think I heard someone mention it was underneath the Temple of Dibella, in the big crag in the center of the city.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysNotAtShrineTalosTopicTopic: Where's the Shrine of Talos?

Cell.Text: No. I was just getting some fresh air. Had one too many pints of mead at the Silver-Blood Inn.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysNotAtShrineAttackTopicTopic: Do you know anything about the attack?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> You want answers? Well so do I. So does everyone in this city. | A man goes crazy in the market. Everyone knows he's a Forsworn agent. Guards do nothing. Nothing but clean up the mess.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysShrineTopic02: I'm not doing anything yet.

Cell.Text: [S] This has been going on for years. And all I've been able to find is murder and blood. I need help. | Please. You find out why Margret was attacked, who's behind Weylin and the Forsworn, and I'll pay you for any information you bring me.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysBlockingShrineBranch01Topic03: You want me to find out why.

Cell.Text: [S] You want to walk away? Fine. But there's going to be no justice for Margret. No one to care what happened to her.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysBlockingShrineBranch01Topic04: I don't have time for this nonsense.

Cell.Text: She's not from Markarth. The air about her screamed "outsider." | Visitors to the city usually stay at the Silver-Blood Inn.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysMargetTopic: What do you know about Marget?

Cell.Text: He was one of the smelter workers. I used to have a job down there myself, casting silver ingots. | I never knew much about Weylin, except he lives in the Warrens, like all the other workers.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysWeylinTopic: Who was Weylin? Where did he live?

Cell.Text: They're remnants of the old rulers of Markarth. Natives of the Reach. Followers of the old ways. | The Nords drove them out of the city. Ulfric Stormcloak and his men. That was about 20 years ago. | But somehow they're still in this city, and they're killing people, almost at random.

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysForswornTopic: Who are the Forsworn?

Cell.Text: Yes. It all started when I was a boy. My father owned one of the mines. Rare for anyone who isn't a Nord. | He was killed. Guards said it was just a madman, but everyone knew the murderer was a member of the Forsworn. | I've been trying to find out why ever since. Gotten nowhere so far, and then I got married. Have a child of my own on the way. | I swore I was going to just give up, for my child's sake, but it's like my father's ghost is haunting me. Asking me "Why?"

Node.Caption: MS01EltrysWhyTopic: You've looked into these murders?

Cell.Text: [S] So the clues point to the Treasury House, then. That makes sense. Thonar is involved in every facet of the city. | Here's the gold I promised. Keep following the trail and there will be more in it for you.

Node.Caption: MS01MargretEvidenceTopic: Margret was investigating Thonar Silver-Blood.

Cell.Text: [S] Nepos the Nose? He's been in Markarth forever. And he's well-respected among the natives of the Reach. | Good work. Here's your gold. I have a feeling Nepos gets his own orders, though. If you find out, I'll have more for you.

Node.Caption: MS01WeylinEvidenceTopic: Weylin got his orders from Nepos.
